The paper deals with channel capacity, which is a fundamental concept in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses various types of channels, including point-to-point and interference channels, which are relevant to communication systems. Hence, cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions optimization and coding theorems, which are related to control and systems engineering, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the generalization of the results to a wide class of costs, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
